        "image": "/images/blog/having-a-baby-after-35-what-you-need-to-know.jpg",
        "featured": false,
        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Having a baby at any age can be a wonderful experience, but there are some things to consider if you&#8217;re thinking about having a baby after the age of 35.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">One potential concern is that women&#8217;s fertility tends to decline with age, so there&#8217;s a higher risk of fertility problems and miscarriage.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">However, advances in medical technology have made it possible for many women to have healthy pregnancies at older ages. It&#8217;s important to talk to your doctor about your situation and any potential risks.</p>\n<h2>Risks of having a baby after 35</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are several potential risks to consider if you&#8217;re thinking about having a baby after the age of 35. As mentioned, one of the main concerns is that women&#8217;s fertility tends to decline with age, which can make it harder to conceive and increase the risk of miscarriage.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Other risks may include:</p>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>An increased risk of chromosomal abnormalities in the baby, such as Down syndrome</li>\n<li>A higher risk of preterm birth or low birth weight</li>\n<li>An increased risk of complications during pregnancy and childbirth, such as gestational diabetes or pre-eclampsia</li>\n<li>A higher risk of having a cesarean delivery</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Know that these risks are not guaranteed to happen and that many women have healthy pregnancies at older ages. However, it&#8217;s important to be aware of these potential risks and discuss them with your doctor before deciding on having a baby.</p>\n<h2>Tips Risks of having a baby after 35</h2>\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>Visit your doctor for a pre-pregnancy checkup. Your doctor can help you assess your overall health and identify any potential risks or concerns.</li>\n<li>Start taking prenatal vitamins. This can help ensure that you and your baby get the necessary nutrients for a healthy pregnancy.</li>\n<li>Eat a healthy, balanced diet. This can help support your health and your baby&#8217;s development.</li>\n<li>Avoid alcohol, tobacco, and drugs. These substances can be harmful to your health and your baby&#8217;s development.</li>\n<li>Get regular exercise. This can help improve your overall health and reduce the risk of complications during pregnancy.</li>\n<li>Manage any chronic conditions you may have. This can help reduce the risk of complications during pregnancy.</li>\n<li>Get your vaccinations up to date. This can help protect you and your baby from serious illnesses.</li>\n<li>Consider genetic testing. This can help identify any potential risks or concerns related to your age or your family history.</li>\n<li>Plan for a healthy pregnancy. This can include making lifestyle changes, such as quitting smoking or reducing stress.</li>\n<li>Learn about the changes your body will go through during pregnancy. This can help you prepare for the physical and emotional challenges of pregnancy.</li>\n<li>Talk to your partner and family members about your plans. This can help ensure that you have support and help during your pregnancy.</li>\n<li>Take childbirth classes. These classes can help you learn about the labor and delivery process and prepare for the birth of your baby.</li>\n<li>Create a birth plan. A birth plan can help you communicate your preferences and wishes for your labor and delivery with your healthcare provider.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Final words</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Stay positive and focused on your health and your baby&#8217;s health. Pregnancy at any age can be a wonderful experience, and staying positive and focused can help you have a healthy pregnancy and a healthy baby.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Also, throughout the pregnancy, stay in touch with your doctor. Follow their advice and recommendations. Report any sign of discomfort or problems. If you have any concerns, ask them questions.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3683.2343059419595!2d88.4076363149602!3d22.60772398516473!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3a0275f9be146665%3A0xe1777ac71c51567a!2sDr.%20Vinita%20Khemani%20-%20Best%20Gynecologist%20in%20Kolkata%2C%20Infertility%20specialist!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1646216771079!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n          \n          \n        </div>\n<!--        <div class=\"contact-right\">\n         <?php// comments_template(); ?>"
