        "id": "48",
        "slug": "6-signs-you-could-have-pcos",
        "title": "6 Signs You Could Have PCOS",
        "excerpt": "You missed a period or two and you are sure you are not pregnant. Unpredictable menstrual cycles? It could be something more serious like PCOS.",
        "category": "PCOS",
        "readTime": "4 min read",
        "date": "Jan 1, 2022",
        "image": "/images/blog/6-signs-you-could-have-pcos.png",
        "featured": false,
        "content": "<p>You missed a period or two and you are sure you are not pregnant. Unpredictable menstrual cycles? You might be thinking it’s due to stress but it could be something more serious like polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS).</p>\n<p>PCOS (also sometimes referred as PCOD) is much more common than you think. More than 1 in 20 females of child bearing age are affected by it. To shed some light on this silent disease, here are the most common not-so-obvious signs of this hormonal disorder. If you&#8217;re experiencing any of these symptoms, seek advice from best gynaecologist in Kolkata and get them evaluated.</p>\n<h3>1. Irregular menstrual cycles</h3>\n<p>Unpredictable menstrual cycles or skipping several periods are one of the hallmarks of PCOS. Having irregular periods or more likely, skipping multiple periods could be a sign of a hormonal imbalance like PCOS. In fact irregular periods are considered one of the primary symptom of PCOS.</p>\n<h3>2. You&#8217;re having trouble getting pregnant.</h3>\n<p>In PCOS the balance between several hormones in your body becomes disturbed. The exact cause of this is not known but the whole process of release of eggs from your ovary goes haywire. So it&#8217;s no surprise that PCOS is one of the most common causes of infertility. With proper treatment and guidance many patients can still get pregnant.</p>\n<h3>3. Crazy hair growing in unexpected places.</h3>\n<p>Excessive hormones called ‘Androgen’ stimulate hair growth on the face, chin, or parts of the body where men usually have hair. If left untreated there can be significant thinning of hair and loss of scalp hair. Let the best gynaecologist near you guide you through your problems.</p>\n<h3>4. Dark ring around your neck</h3>\n<p>PCOS can lead to darkening of skin around your neck creases, in the groin, and underneath breasts</p>\n<h3>5. Your belly is getting bigger and you don&#8217;t know why</h3>\n<p>You look into the mirror and blame yourself for having that extra bite of chocolate. But you may be totally unaware that it may be due to insulin resistance developing in your body due to high levels of this hormone. Again PCOS is here to blame. A quick examination and workup of your blood parameters will help your gynaecologist determine if you have PCOS.</p>\n<h3>6. Everyone hates acne</h3>\n<p>The high levels of androgen hormones cause eruptions of those unwanted acnes. Most females try to treat these with home remedies but the underlying cause is missed.</p>\n<p>PCOS or PCOD can be difficult to diagnose and treat. Early treatment is recommended to avoid serious complications like infertility. Get advice from the best Gynecologist in Kolkata for PCOS.</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n          \n          \n        </div>\n<!--        <div class=\"contact-right\">\n         <?php// comments_template(); ?>"
